ners and project participants.</p>\n<p>Specific duties may include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Creating project bibliographies;</li>\n<li>Researching existing projects and platforms for working with and/or producing digital texts;</li>\n<li>Researching editorial theories and workflows established by existing projects and applying to upcoming projects;</li>\n<li>Drafting project documentation and publications;</li>\n<li>Researching and developing contact information for potential project partners;</li>\n<li>Assisting in planning and putting on project meetings and consultations;</li>\n<li>Other duties as determined by project leadership.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Required experience and qualifications:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>BA in a related field;</li>\n<li>Humanities-based research experience;</li>\n<li>Experience working in a team environment.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This position will be based in the Electronic Textual Cultures Lab at the University of Victoria. The ideal candidate will be a self-starter who can work both independently and with a consultative research team.</p>\n<p>The salary for this position will conform with the standard Graduate Research Assistant rates, and the term will span approximately 4 to 6 months, beginning in October 2014.</p>\n<p>Applications, comprising a brief cover letter, CV, and the names and contact information for three referees, may be sent electronically to &lt;etcl@uvic.ca&gt;. Applications will be reviewed beginning 6 October, and the position will remain open until a candidate is found.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:84:\"http://etcl.uvic.ca/2014/09/30/job-posting-graduate-student-research-assistant/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"commen