0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"QuickTip\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"gettext\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"say what\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"http://connections-pro.com/?p=290279\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:540:\"<p>All the template available on this site allow you to easily change many text labels by setting a shortcode option. See this FAQ on how to use this feature. This is a great easy to use feature when you just need to change a label while be displayed in the template. However, sometimes you need change ...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://connections-pro.com/2014/05/04/quicktip-easy-text-changing/\">QuickTip: Easy Text Changing</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://connections-pro.com\">Connections</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Steven Zahm\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5097:\"<p>All the template available on this site allow you to easily change many text labels by setting a shortcode option. See this <a title=\"How do I use the str_***** shortcode options?\" href=\"http://connections-pro.com/faqs/how-do-i-use-the-str_-shortcode-options/\">FAQ</a> on how to use this feature. This is a great easy to use feature when you just need to change a label while be displayed in the template. However, sometimes you need change the text label every where the text label is used throughout Connections. Luckily this is very easy to accomplish with Connections and here&#8217;s how&#8230; First, install the <a title=\"Say What? WordPress Plugin\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/say-what/\">Say What?</a> plugin.</p>\n<p>After you install and activate the <a title=\"Say What? WordPress Plugin\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/say-what/\">Say What?</a> plugin there will be a new menu item added under the Tools admin menu named <strong>Text changes</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-290280\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/say-what-text-changes.png\" alt=\"Say What? Admin Menu\" width=\"320\" height=\"150\" /></p>\n<p>When you go to this page for the first time there will not be much of anything to see, no instructions or anything to guide you on what to do next. Do not let this discourage you because it is a very simple to use tool. The first step is to identify the text label you want to change in Connections. For the purposes of this QuickTip, we&#8217;ll assume you want to change the text label for the Biographical Info metabox in the admin.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-290281\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/connections-bio-metabox-header.png\" alt=\"Biographical Info Metabox Header\" width=\"200\" height=\"150\" /></p>\n<p>Go to the <strong>Tools : Text changes</strong> admin page and click the <strong>Add New</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-290282\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/say-what-add-new-button.png\" alt=\"Say What?: Add New Button\" width=\"229\" height=\"34\" /></p>\n<p>After you click the button you&#8217;ll b presented with a new screen asking for the <strong>Original string</strong>, <strong>Text Domain, Text context</strong> and <strong>Replacement string</strong>.  The Original string is where you enter the text label from Connections, in this case it will be &#8220;Biographical Info&#8221;, without the quotes. The Replacement string will be anything you want. We&#8217;ll change it to &#8220;Business Information&#8221;, again, without the quotes. Explaining the Domain option is out of scope for this QuickTip, but basically it is the plugin ID for text replacement for translations. This ID for Connections is &#8220;connections&#8221;, without the quotes. The Text context field, leave it blank. After you fill in the the form, it should look like the screen capture below.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-305865 size-full\" src=\"http://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/say-what-add-new-replacement-string.png\" alt=\"Say What?: Add New Replacement String\" width=\"231\" height=\"372\" /></p>\n<p>Click the <strong>Add</strong> button. Now visit the Connections : Add Entry admin page and scroll to the &#8220;Biographical Info&#8221; metabox. You should now see the text label has been changed to &#8220;Business Information&#8221;.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-290285\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/connections-bio-metabox-header-business-info.png\" alt=\"Biographical Info Metabox Header Changed to Business Information\" width=\"200\" height=\"150\" /></p>\n<p>The great thing about using the <a title=\"Say What? WordPress Plugin\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/say-what/\">Say What?</a> plugin is that making text changes which are update safe. You can even use this plugin to change text label in plugins other than Connections, you only need to identify the what the plugin <strong>Domain</strong> is. Additionally, this will change &#8220;Biographical Info&#8221; in any templates that show it. If the template shows the &#8220;Biographical Info&#8221; text label and it has the option to to change it, you can still use that option to override the changes made by the <a title=\"Say What? WordPress Plugin\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/say-what/\">Say What?</a> plugin.</p>\n<p>Now, this is pretty important&#8230;</p>\n<p>This QuickTip will not work with many strings [text] in the templates as this QuickTip pertains to the core Connections plugin. So, with templates, there is an alternative method. To learn more about that alternative method, please see this <a title=\"How do I use the str_***** shortcode options?\" href=\"http://connections-pro.com/faqs/how-do-i-use-the-str_-shortcode-options/\">FAQ</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://connections-pro.com/2014/05/04/quicktip-easy-text-changing/\">QuickTip: Easy Text Changing</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://connections-pro.com\">Connections</a>.</p>\n<img src=\"//feeds.feedburner.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~4/Irnh9Yyc1qc\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"http://connections-pro.com/2014/05/04/quicktip-easy-text-changing/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"http://connections-pro.com/2014/05/04/quicktip-easy-text-changing/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"[UPDATED] Introducing Link\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~3/qVHN7aruqeo/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"http://connections-pro.com/2013/01/07/introducing-link-updated/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 08 Jan 2013 02:56:14 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Announcement\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Connections\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"add-on\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"http://connections-pro.com/?p=248739\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:549:\"<p>UPDATE: To bring even more value to those who purchased the Pro Add-on Pack and Pro Pack they will have Link automatically added to their purchase when it is released! While not quite ready for release, it&#8217;s close enough to announce&#8230; What is Link? Link is add-on plugin that is the solution to the very ...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://connections-pro.com/2013/01/07/introducing-link-updated/\">[UPDATED] Introducing Link</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://connections-pro.com\">Connections</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Steven Zahm\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2760:\"<p><strong>UPDATE:</strong><br />\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">To bring even more value to those who purchased the Pro Add-on Pack and Pro Pack they will have Link automatically added to their purchase when it is released!</span></p>\n<p>While not quite ready for release, it&#8217;s close enough to announce&#8230;</p>\n<p>What is Link? Link is add-on plugin that is the solution to the very often requested feature of being able to link a registered WordPress user to a Connections entry. Ok, what does this really mean for you? This will allow registered users on your site to maintain their own entry within Connections, either moderated or not. This effectively turns Connections into a member directory plugin! Well, the first steps.</p>\n<p>How does it work? You install Link like you would any other plugin and activate it. Link has no user interface of its own, it works silently in the background. Well, sort of. It will add a new menu item under the User admin menu named, &#8220;Your Directory Entry&#8221;. On this page you&#8217;ll find the form you&#8217;ve come to love from the Connections : Add Entry admin page, just tweaked slightly. The only settings that you will need to set after activation are on the Connections : Roles admin page. You&#8217;ll need to chose whether your registered users can add / edit their entry moderated or not. Now your registered users will be able to maintain their own entry.</p>\n<p>Sounds great, but I already have a bunch of registered users and entries in Connections, how are those going to get &#8220;linked&#8221;? Silently in the background when your registered users login, Link will check the entries in Connections for an email address that matches the one in their user account. If a match is found, Link will &#8220;link&#8221; them together.</p>\n<p>To bring you Link, some challenges had to be overcome. Connections was designed so its entries were not linked to users to offer you greater flexibility in creating your directories. So there were workflow issues that had to be resolved such as commingling regular entries and &#8220;linked&#8221; entries, ensuring that once a link was created that it would not be lost by an admin edit, and making sure it would not be possible for someone to edit an entry that didn&#8217;t belong to them.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m sold. How much longer? As always I&#8217;m running behind schedule, but it will definitely be this month.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://connections-pro.com/2013/01/07/introducing-link-updated/\">[UPDATED] Introducing Link</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://connections-pro.com\">Connections</a>.</p>\n<img src=\"//feeds.feedburner.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~4/qVHN7aruqeo\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:68:\"http://connections-pro.com/2013/01/07/introducing-link-updated/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http:/