 a shortcode option. The category select feature is pretty neat, if I may say so. The user can click on the box and just start typing to search for categories, then they simply click the ones in which they would like to be listed. If the user makes a mistake or changes their mind about being listed in a specific category the user simply clicks the &#8216;x&#8217; to remove that selection. What&#8217;s great about this is that this method easily scales to a large number of categories without taking up huge amount of screen space while being very user friendly. I&#8217;ve updated the <a href=\"/demo/extension/form/\" title=\"Connections Form Demo\">demo</a>, go give it a spin!</p>\n\n<div class=\"wp_syntax\"><table><tr><td class=\"code\"><pre class=\"php\" style=\"font-family:monospace;\"><span style=\"color: #666666; font-style: italic;\">/*\n * Example 1\n * Change the default entry type\n */</span>\n<span style=\"color: #009900;\">&#91;</span>connections_form default_type<span style=\"color: #339933;\">=</span><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">\'organization\'</span><span style=\"color: #009900;\">&#93;</span>\n&nbsp;\n<span style=\"color: #666666; font-style: italic;\">/*\n * Example 2\n * Disable the Category data type\n */</span>\n<span style=\"color: #009900;\">&#91;</span>connections_form category<span style=\"color: #339933;\">=</span><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">\'false\'</span><span style=\"color: #009900;\">&#93;</span></pre></td></tr></table></div>\n\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://connections-pro.com/2012/04/01/pro-module-update-form-0-2/\">Pro Module Update: Form 0.2</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://connections-pro.com\">Connections</a>.</p>\n<img src=\"//feeds.feedburner.com/~r/connections-pro-modules/~4/r0SPIk8X1QM\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s: