</b> is a social knowledge creation environment facilitating and supporting communication, collaboration, and digital project creation for research communities of the Middle Ages and the Renaissance. See our <strong>About Us</strong> page for a complete description.[/accordion_item]\n\n[accordion_item active=\"no\" title=\"How do I start with Iter Community?\" accordion=\"accordion\"]Before you do anything on the website, please read our terms of service and our privacy policies. If you agree to the policies, then an ideal place to start would be to explore the blog for current information on Iter Community. You could also start on the <strong>Past Conferences</strong> page to view previous conferences relevant to Iter Community. [/accordion_item]\n\n[accordion_item active=\"no\" title=\"Does being a member of Iter Community cost anything?\" accordion=\"accordion\"]There is no fee to join the Iter Community website. Most features of the website require a free WordPress account.[/accordion_item]\n\n[accordion_item active=\"no\" title=\"Who has access to Iter Community?\" accordion=\"accordion\"]Anyone may view the Iter Community. Your access to Iter Community relies on your user role. See the Wiki Help Doc on user roles for more information.[/accordion_item]\n\n[accordion_item active=\"no\" title=\"How do I connect with other members of Iter Community?\" accordion=\"accordion\"]You can connect with other users via the members page. The members can be accessed under the People tab at the top of any page on Iter Community.[/accordion_item]\n\n[accordion_item active=\"no\" title=\"Can I invite a colleague to Iter Community?\" accordion=\"accordion\"]You may invite anyone to Iter Community, but access to the website depends on his or her user role.[/accordion_item]\n\n[accordion_item active=\"no\" title=\"Who has access to Iter Community?\" accordion=\"accordion\"]Anyone may access the Iter Community website. However, only specific users with certain user roles can modify the content of Iter Community. Please see the Wiki Help Doc explaining user roles.[/accordion_item]\n\n[accordion_item active=\"no\" title=\"What are Iter Community user roles?\" accordion=\"accordion\"]User roles establish a ranking system on Iter Community. Site administrators hold the highest ranks, while most users hold the lowest rank. Please see the Wiki Help Doc explaining user roles for more detailed descriptions of each role.[/accordion_item]\n\n[accordion_item active=\"no\" title=\"How do I post an event in the Events Calendar?\" accordion=\"accordion\"]Please see the Wiki Help Doc explaining how one can create an event in the calendar.[/accordion_item]\n\n[accordion_item active=\"no\" title=\"Who should I invite to be in a Group? How will I know if I&#39;ve been invited into somebody else&#39;s Group?\" accordion=\"accordion\"]If you are creating a private group, you should only invite the select number of people to be in the group. In a public group, anyone can join without requiring an invitation. If you have been invited to a group, you will receive a WordPress notification.[/accordion_item]\n\n[accordion_item active=\"no\" title=\"I want to upload previous conference material to the \'Past Conferences\' section. How do I do that?\" accordion=\"accordion\"]Create a page with the conference information and set the page to be the child of \"Past Conferences.\" To set pages in a parent/child relationship, navigate to Page Attributes when editing a page, and select the page you wish to be the parent.[/accordion_item]\n\n[accordion_item active=\"no\" title=\"How can I subscribe to new posts on Iter Community?\" accordion=\"accordion\"]We are developing an answer to this question.[/accordion_item]\n\n[accordion_item active=\"no\" title=\"What are the privacy regulations for Iter Community? Are you going to sell my information to nefarious marketers?\" accordion=\"accordion\"]Iter Community will not sell your information to any unknown third parties. Identifiable personal information will not be disclosed to a third party unless required to by law. Please read the privacy policies page for more information.[/accordion_item]\n\n[accordion_item active=\"no\" title=\"How do I send questions, comments, or complaints to the developers of Iter Community?\" accordion=\"accordion\"]You may send a private message to any site administrator. To send a message, navigate to the members page and click on an administrator profile, then click private message. Send your message and the administrator will respond as soon as possible.[/accordion_item]\n\n[accordion_item active=\"no\" title=\"How do I set up a project with Iter Community?\" accordion=\"accordion\"]Navigate to the Projects Application page and fill out the application for project space on Iter Community. Please see the Wiki Help Doc explaining explaining project applications.[/accordion_item]\n\n[accordion_item active=\"no\" title=\"Where is my stuff stored? Can I access it at any time?\" accordion=\"accordion\"]We are developing an answer to this question.[/accordion_item]\n[/accordion]','FAQs','','inherit','open','open','','6821-autosave-v1','','','2015-05-22 22:14:59','2015-05-22 22:14:59','',6821,'http://www.itercom.org/6821-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(7915,3,'2015-05-22 22:08:34','2015-05-22 22:08:34','<h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>\r\n[accordion] [accordion_item active=\"yes\" title=\"What is Iter Community?\" accordion=\"accordion\"]<b>Iter Community</b> is a social knowledge creation environment facilitating and supporting communication, collaboration, and digital project creation for research communities of the Middle Ages and the Renaissance. See our <strong>About Us</strong> page for a complete description.[/accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[accordion_item active=\"no\" title=\"How do I start with Iter Community?\" accordion=\"accordion\"]Before you do anything on the website, please read our terms of service and our privacy policies. If you agree to the polic